Which version are you using? The demo site is using jQuery 1.8.3 (not 1.9) and webshims 1.9.6.

In case you want to use DOM-APIs, it is always best to load webshims as fast as possible a delay the ready event, (webshims delays the ready event by default, if it is called before DOM-Ready) until everything is implemented. (DOM-APIs are all $.prop methods or special methods like play/checkValidity).

In case you only want to use Markup-API (i.e. simple HTML or $.attr), you won't need to delay the ready event.

From your code I assume, you are only using Markup-APIs and your problem is, that the new dynamic content isn't "polyfilled". To get this done, simply call updatePolyfill on the container of the new content. A short description is documented [here](http://afarkas.github.com/webshim/demos/demos/shiv.html#dynamic) and [here](http://afarkas.github.com/webshim/demos/index.html#polyfill-abstractions):

```
$.webshims.polyfill('forms forms-ext');
$(function() {
    $("#load-div").load('myfile.html', function() { // callback for after load is done
        $(this).updatePolyfill();
    });
});
```

In case you don't want the ready event delayed, you can use the following options (This means, that DOM might be faster ready, but it's not safe to use HTML5 DOM-APIs), which is documented [here](http://afarkas.github.com/webshim/demos/index.html#polyfill-options):

```
$.webshims.setOptions({ 
    waitReady: false
});
$.webshims.polyfill('forms forms-ext');
$(function() {
    //load after DOM-READY but before new content is arrived (better against FOUC)
    $("#load-div").load('myfile.html', function() { // callback for after load is done
        $(this).updatePolyfill();
    });
});
```

