But you simply should look how responsive your site feels using this. It's not werid at all. JS can not get positions and real dimension on hidden elements (display: none) (see also documentation [re-rendering shadowdom](http://afarkas.github.io/webshim/demos/index.html#polyfill-abstractions). Therefore webshims needs to re-calculate this. I might improve performance here with future releases. If you see that performance is really bad. You can fully disable width calculation:

``` js
webshims.setOptions('forms-ext', {
    widgets: {
        calculateWidth: false
    }
});
```

In this case you have to set width/margins for native **and** polyfilled elements your own.

